description:
&lt;h1&gt;&lt;strong&gt;First Contact Physiotherapist with Lancaster Primary Care Network (Lancaster Medical Practice and Queen Square Medical Practice)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;Salary: £33,396 - £48,023 per annum, pro rata&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;HOURS: 37.5 hours per week&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Permanent contract&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;2 x roles available (1 to start as soon as possible, 1 to start April 2021)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Are you passionate about delivering high quality care to patients, and are looking to develop your career in primary care? Then this could be the role for you!&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Lancaster Primary Care Network is looking for a First Contact Physiotherapists to join our multi disciplinary teams of GPs, Advanced Clinical Practitioners, Clinical Pharmacists and Social Prescribers. The PCN has a large population of around 80,000 patients.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;We are looking for a motivated individual who will be able to manage their own workload, work independently and build strong relationships across the practices. The successful candidate will also demonstrate good communication skills, with a flexible approach and good use of initiative.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Lancaster Medical Practice is open between 8am and 6.30pm Monday - Friday. Our extended hours provisions run from 6.30pm - 8pm Monday to Friday, and from 8am - 12noon on a Saturday at our Rosebank site.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a team we are made up of a Lead Nurse Partner, ACPs (including a Paramedic, a Physiotherapist and 2 Mental Health Practitioners), Clinical Pharmacists, Practice Nurses, an Assistant Practitioner and a team of HCAs. We work alongside a friendly and dynamic team of GP partners and Associate GPs.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;LMP offers a range of benefits including NHS pension, a generous holiday entitlement (including Bank Holidays), NHS discounts and offers to name a few.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For more information please read the attached job description and person specification. Please also take the time to read the attached privacy notice.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further information or an informal chat about this role please contact lmp.hr@gp-p81002.nhs.uk.&lt;/p&gt;
